εἰς τὸ κοινόβι(ον) ἀββᾶ Παμοῦν ἐν τῷ Ὄρι (l. Ὄρει) Π̣άεε. (P.Oxy. 27 2480 119-120, 565-566 CE);

a list of offerings to religious institutions, a prosphora is made to Mega Oros
εἰς τὸ Μέγα Ὄρος. (P.Oxy. 67 4620 18, 5th-6th cent. CE). As a toponym, this place is also found in a 7th-8th century tax list (P.Leid.Inst. 80 v, 2. 7);
／ χ(ωρίον) Μ(ε)γ(άλου) Ὄρου̣ς. Furthemore, an unpublished papyrus from Oxyrhynchos (inv. no. 68.6B.25/F(3)a) cited by M. Mountford in her unpublished doctoral thesis, mentions a payment made by a pronoetes to Mega Oros.
Mountford, M. (2012), Documentary papyri from Roman and Byzantine Oxyrhynchus, unpub. PhD thesis, University College London, London: 207, accessed online on 17.02.2023 at:
